<br>
If they are alive, the warrior would love nothing better than to introduce them to her blade.  But, not right away.  She wants to teach them a lesson in vengeance first.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 427<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/03 8:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Old Times and Old Ways resurface</span><hr size=1>  Dawn grinned, running her hand over her face a moment to take away abit of the grogginess that accompanied her use of magick.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Romans. Easy.&quot; <br>
<br>
 Dawn nodded, taking two swords from her sides, she stuck them into the ground. They were well made, silver hilts; polished in beautiful form and texture, with midnight black blades, the sharpened tips jagged and tempting. She stuck them into the ground, pulling another sword from her back, and doing the same, it was of the same material only gold in color.<br>
<br>
 &quot;Swords.. they're good at combatant forms like that.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn pulled from the scabbard, a bow, and quill of arrows, tossing them to Hippolyte.<br>
<br>
 &quot;They aren't as skilled with arrows. Good aim, easy take outs.&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn's eyes twinkled with every weapon she pulled, her daggers from her ankles were laid out next to the swords, and a knife from a scabbard around her thigh was held in her hands.<br>
<br>
 &quot;They're not as dangerous as you think. I've killed an entire army before. What's your plan?&quot;<br>
<br>
 Dawn stretched, tossing the knife around in her hand. Blade, hilt, blade, hilt. The blade or hilt never pausing long enough to hit her palm.<br>
<br>
 Emeralds glanced to the two women, a comforting smile was offered to them, before her eyes turned back to Hippolyte. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dawnithinia>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/15/03 8:21:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#993300>(2/15/03 8:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gathering of the Amazons</span><hr size=1> Perhaps it was because every amazon can sense another. Or maybe it was because Hippolyte gave off such a presence to others. Depending on the amazon came the reason they came to her.<br>
<br>
Hippolyte never once turned her back on Alysia. Even when Aly came to Themiscrya an ex Roman, it was Hippolyte who took her in, trained her, it was Hippolyte that was there when Alysia claimed Scynthia. And it was Hippolyte who stood at her side when they organized the Amazon Nation Alliance.<br>
<br>
Though the Scynthian had been away from the Nation for a time now, she felt Hippolyte's presence back in battle, and she'd never allow her athelfi to fight alone.<br>
<br>
She appeared stepping through the woods, right in front of them. She came barefoot and wearing her amazon leathers which compared to most Northern tribes, left little to the imagination. Two large white wolves stood at either side of their Queen. Scythe and Aeceus. Alysia smiled to Hippolyte and bowed to a knee speaking the word &quot;Vasilissa&quot;. And both wolves bowed their heads before Hippolyte as well.<br>
<br>
Alysia rose and smiled to her old friend. <br>
<br>
