<br>
Cassandra watched and then answered Lysia, &quot;Just men...I mean they look like Roman men I suppose.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then in walked Alysia with her trusted companions.  Hippolyte smiled and saluted her athelfi.  &quot;Seems Artemis's arrows are awakening the souls of many amazons to our calling.&quot;  She grinned at Alysia.  Hippolyte knew Alysia too felt something happening.  The shamanic nature of the Scythians was well known.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is a village of men...Roman men.  From what Cassandra and Kara have told me...they kidnapped their ..so called &quot;wives&quot;.  Building a town between here and Troy.  But, what they didn't know... is the land is just on this side of the Amazon Nation.  Our land....and as these women are captive.....as amazons..we owe them a chance for freedom.  To taste what we taste...by the blessings of our Gods and Ancients.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;It will be simple...as we did in the past...we will make them fear these woods.  For the wild beasts that live here..do not take a liking to them and their ways.  We will don the masks of our animals....well at least some of us.&quot;  She nodded to Dawn.  &quot;We will work at night...freeing the women...slowely..one by one.   In effect...the &quot;beasts&quot; will take their women...and &quot;eat&quot; the men.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cassandra and Kara suddenly came clue to how the old stories were made.  The wild beasts from childhood...were actually Amazons.  Amazons who freed the women from oppressive villages.<br>
<br>
 <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

Once a Vasilissa...now only a priestess and warrior of war....she wanders the amazon nation and lands of the Greeks searching the future for the past....until the day shame is no longer hers...and she can take her place in history ..once again. 
